Thermo Electron Corp is raising 75 mlndlrs via an offering of convertible subordinated debentures due2012 with a 5-3/4 pct coupon and par pricing, said lead managerShearson Lehman Brothers Inc.    The debentures are convertible into the company's stock at30.50 dlrs per share, representing a premium of 25.77 pct overthe stock price when terms on the debt were set.    Non-callable for two years, the issue is rated Ba-3 byMoody's Investors and BB by Standard and Poor's. Drexel Burnhamand Tucker Anthony co-managed the deal. Reuter&#3;